# ── Trailing slash normalisation: ALL article & deep pages (301, not auto-307) ──
# ⚠️  STAGED 2026-06-09 — VERIFY ON A PREVIEW DEPLOY BEFORE TRUSTING IN PRODUCTION.
#
# WHY THIS EXISTS:
#   Astro runs trailingSlash:'never'. Cloudflare auto-redirects /page/ → /page, but
#   with a 307 (TEMPORARY). A 307 tells Google the move isn't permanent, so old
#   WordPress trailing-slash URLs never drop out of "Crawled - currently not indexed"
#   and ranking signal never consolidates onto the canonical no-slash URL. That is the
#   root cause of the growing not-indexed count (35→190, Mar→Jun 2026).
#
#   The depth-1 rules ABOVE (e.g. /business/ → /business) already prove that explicit
#   _redirects rules override Cloudflare's auto-307 on this site (verified live: 301).
#   These placeholder rules extend the SAME proven fix to article-level URLs
#   (/category/slug/) which can't be enumerated by hand.
#
# ORDER MATTERS: these are catch-alls and MUST stay at the very bottom of the file.
#   Cloudflare matches top-to-bottom, first match wins — so every specific redirect
#   above (deprecated cats, /category/ prefix, broken links) fires FIRST. Each :name
#   placeholder matches exactly one path segment, so these only fire on URLs that still
#   carry a trailing slash after the specific rules have had their chance.
#
# HOW TO VERIFY after the preview deploy is live (replace <preview-host>):
#   curl -sI https://<preview-host>/business/customer-relationship-management-crm/ \
#     | grep -iE '^HTTP|^location'
#   EXPECT:  HTTP/2 301   +   location: /business/customer-relationship-management-crm
#   (If you see 307, the placeholder rules did not take precedence — revert this block
#    and fall back to enumerating the ~100 article URLs explicitly.)

/:a/           /:a           301
/:a/:b/        /:a/:b        301
/:a/:b/:c/     /:a/:b/:c     301
